-- Brussels Airlines Gets Permits for Congo Subsidiary, L’Echo Says
-- B y   J i m   B r u n s d e n
-- 2012-02-18T11:29:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-18/brussels-airlines-gets-permits-for-congo-subsidiary-l-echo-says.html
Brussels Airlines NV , the Belgian
airline that is 45 percent owned by  Deutsche Lufthansa AG (LHA) , has
received the necessary permits from the  Democratic Republic  of
Congo to set up a subsidiary carrier in the country,  L’Echo
reported , citing Managing Director Michel Meyfroidt.  The carrier, Korongo, will be set up by Brussels Airlines
in partnership with investment company George Forrest
International and other private investors, according to the
airline’s  website . It will operate on regional routes in the
African country, as well as to several other cities including
Johannesburg, L’Echo said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jim Brunsden in Brussels at 
 jbrunsden@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  